The paper deals with the problem of maximizing the sum-rate of wireless users in a communication system, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of rate splitting multiple access (RSMA) and successive decoding techniques also suggests a focus on system design and optimization (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions simulation results and comparisons with other multiple access techniques, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories.
